 by mary kay henry personal details born  november   age  west orange new jersey us political party democratic spouses jane perkins divorced children matt cassie alma mater university of pennsylvania  andrew l andy stern born november   is the former president of the then million member service employees international union seiu he is now president emeritus of seiu which grew by more than  million workers during his tenure called a “courageous visionary leader who charted a bold new course for american unionism”  stern has been featured on  minutes and cnn as fox news power player of the week and on the covers of the new york times magazine fortune and businessweek under sterns leadership seiu became the largest union in the aflcio and the fastest growing union in the world then after promoting a debate on the future of american labor in a bold move seiu left the aflcio with six  other unions and formed a new labor alliancechange to win stern was a senior fellow at columbia university and is now a senior fellow at the economic security project stern has been described by cbs news as the most important labor boss in america stern is unapologetic about holding private equity firms accountable questioning business and political leaders practices and competing to build seius membership we like to say we use the power of persuasion first if it doesnt work we try the persuasion of power stern supported federal legislation to create universal health careobamacare expansion of union ranks via the employee free choice act and regulations on business profit sharing and retirement security for employees and more equitable tax policy he was a presidential appointee on the national commission on fiscal responsibility and reform best known as simpsonbowles he is chair of the board of the broad center and a board member of the open society foundations and the hillman foundation in march  stern was the alice b grant labor leader in residence at the cornell university school of industrial and labor relations he is the author of two books a country that works   and raising the floor how a universal basic income can renew our economy and rebuild the american dream  the ft wrote in its review of raising the floor technology as stern sees it overwhelms everything else including the american dream itself while he is persuaded that automation and information technology will make many jobs obsolete and thereby hurt workers he does not suggest holding back technological change he looks for policies to make the unpredictable lifestyle of a gig worker more tolerable — above all universal basic income where a regular cash amount is given to every citizen regardless of whether or not they work  contents  early life and career  internet and new media  a country that works  family  political influence  controversy  resignation  references  external links early life and careeredit he grew up jewish in west orange new jersey where his father was a lawyer he began college as a business major at the university of pennsylvanias wharton school of business but ultimately graduated in  with a ba in education and urban planning stern began his career as a welfare caseworker and member of the seiu local  in  eventually being elected president in  of his pennsylvania local in  he was elected as the youngest member in its history to the unions international executive board and in  the unions thenpresident john sweeney put him in charge of its organizing efforts in  stern was elected to the presidency of the union after launching a national debate aimed at uniting the  out of  american workers who have no organization at work seiu along with the teamsters announced on july   that they were disaffiliating from the aflcio stern led seiu out of the aflcio and founded change to win a sixmillionmember federation of seven major unions dedicated to giving workers a voice at their jobs stern was a senior fellow at the georgetown public policy institute from    from  he has served as a senior fellow at the richard paul richman center for business law and public policy at columbia university in  stern authored a book with lee kravitz entitled raising the floor in which he makes the case for a universal basic income internet and new mediaedit stern has embraced political organizing via the internet in the wake of the howard dean campaign which his union endorsed in fall of  he launched an online contest called since sliced bread that awarded  for the best new economic idea in america since  stern has been a contributing blogger at the huffington post stern has been a key figure in financing the online grassroots netroots community along with dean george soros simon rosenberg and andrew s rappaport to funnel a progressive agenda to liberal bloggers through sterns initiative a new media team was formed at seiu in the late summer of  the unions website was completely redesigned and relaunched shortly after a country that worksedit in the book a country that works free press stern calls for unions to be the dominant vehicles for the promotion of social reforms including espousing the benefits of increased taxation on the wealthy and universal health care on october   he appeared on the colbert report  to promote his new book a country that works on october  he appeared on democracy now to promote the book familyedit stern is divorced from jane perkins a former head of the environmental network friends of the earth they had two children matt and cassie cassie died in  he is married to jennifer johnson communications director at the center for food action in new jersey political influenceedit during the years of sterns leadership the seiu became the largest political action committee in the united states and funneled vast amounts of financing to the democratic party and its candidates far outnumbering the contributions of other unions during the last two election cycles seiu contributed  million to the  presidential campaign of john kerry the union spent another  million on democratic candidates in   million going toward the election of president barack obama with a significant chunk of that money funding doortodoor canvassing and other gotv efforts as well as voter registration stern has been the most frequent visitor to the white house since obamas election between inauguration day and february   stern visited the white house  times stern is referred to as one of the chief architects of healthcare reform in modern healthcare magazine ranking in the top  of the  most powerful people in healthcare stern has been named to modern healthcares annual movers and shakers in healthcare list for five years in a row seiu poured millions into a group called health care for america now which at times fought strongly for universal healthcare including single payer stern was an ardent supporter of the american recovery and reinvestment act of  organized labour portal controversyedit hes arguably the most important labor leader weve had in a long time aggressive and controversial says philip dine an authority on labor issues and author of the recent book state of the unions on january   seiu placed uhw west under trusteeship and dismissed  of the locals executives including president sal rosselli rosselli and other ousted leaders reformed under the national union of healthcare workers and pushed for uhw west members at  facilities to vote to decertify seiu seiu filed a lawsuit in mid alleging that uhw west and nuhw officials embezzled millions of dollars in  former labor secretary ray marshall issued a report acting as hearing officer mr marshall found that the locals president sal rosselli and other union officials had improperly transferred union money to a nonprofit group to use in a feud with the parent union mr marshall also concluded that the local had wrongly hidden  from the parent union by placing the money into a lawyers trust account on march   the united states court of appeals for the ninth circuit affirmed the district court ruling that a jury awarded  individual judgments ranged from  to  and nuhw was assessed damages of  resignationedit stern announced on april   that he would be stepping down as president of the seiu“there’s a time to learn a time to lead and then there’s a time to leave and shortly it will be my time to retire… and end my seiu journey” andy stern april   the conservative blog redstate grudgingly acknowledged sterns importance at the time of his resignation  built an empire of purpleclad followers taken a relatively obscure union of janitors and doormen and turned it into the largest and most powerful privatesector union in america while almost all others have been failing torn apart the aflcio in attempt to make it into something it didn’t want to be put a president of the united states into the oval office and most importantly fulfilled one of the union movement’s main objectives nationalized health care not only did andy’s seiu push for nationalized health care more than any other union when it looked like obamacare was finished a few months ago on january th andy stern is the guy that provided democrats with a path forward  referencesedit  andrew l stern marquis whos who  reproduced in biography resource center farmington hills michigan gale  httpgalenetgalegroupcomservletbiorc fee via fairfax county public library accessed  document number k  a b duke lynne january   love labor loss a childs death stirred andrew stern to challenge himself  and unionism washington post retrieved    andy stern  seiu  retirement mediaite  archived from the original on  june  retrieved    andy stern seiu international president seiu archived from the original on  retrieved    national labor organizations with membership over  infoplease pearson education retrieved  members union  national education association of the united states  service employees international union  us department of labor  aflcio aflcio archived from the original on  retrieved    duke lynne  lo